  "presentation_notes": {
    "opening": "So what's the root cause? It's simple: Your entire data stack only works downstream.",
    "diagram_walkthrough": {
      "upstream": "[Point to left side] Look at the upstream zone—where your data is actually generated. At the edge. In your applications. In your databases. [Pause] There are no tools here. Zero control. Zero visibility. Zero optimization.",
      "arrow": "[Point to arrow] So ALL your data—100% of it, unfiltered—flows into the cloud.",
      "downstream": "[Point to right side] And now look at the downstream zone. THIS is where all your tools live. Snowflake. Databricks. Splunk. Datadog. Fivetran. dbt. [Pause] These are incredible platforms. But they all share one fatal limitation: They only see data AFTER it's already in the cloud.",
      "consequence": "[Point to consequence box] Here's the problem: By the time data reaches your tools, it's already too late. You've already paid to move it. You've already paid to store it. You're locked into processing costs you can't avoid. Every optimization you do—compression, deduplication, sampling—happens AFTER the damage is done."
    },
    "transition": "So the question becomes: What if we could control data BEFORE it reaches these expensive platforms? What if we could filter, transform, and govern it at the source? [Pause] That's what we call 'Upstream Data Control.' Let me show you what that looks like...",
    "pacing": "Spend time on the visual contrast. Let audience absorb the empty left vs. crowded right."
  },
